race.comment: HERAULT (6) settled well back and wound up strongly to finish a long neck adrift over 1400m at Northam. He was heavily bet and couldn't have been more impressive. May has to do it the hard way again, but he'll be fitter again, and the step up to the mile is in his favour. INVINCIBLE THIEF (3) also made up plenty of ground to find a place over this trip on the same day. She has more to give and should be fighting out the finish. LOVE OF FAR FA (5) was quickly back on track missing by 1L at Bunbury over 1705m. She's raced the two before over middle distances and she gets a gear switch on a 9-day return. Hard fit now and is well in the mix. WHO'S TALKING (4) peaks and is heading in the right direction. Has no luck here the latest over 1400m, and draws an inside barrier today. Consider.
